<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="46" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Struma Valley/16: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-14T11:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">May 14,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 14—10:10
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>39. Government decided Saturday night<note n="56" xml:id="d46fn56">May
                                12.</note> to grant drainage contract to combination of Ulen and
                            Company and Monks interests and to the Foundation Company. Total
                            expenditure approximately $40,000,000.</p>
                        <p>[Paraphrase.] The official pressure by the British on behalf of their
                            firm, Boot and Company, was very strong, but it did not succeed in
                            getting the contract. [End paraphrase.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>